Description:
Not Just Another Unit
Positioned at the rear of an immaculate, established block of units on a large plot of approximately 434m2. You will not have to give up the garden as this unit has a lovely expanse of outdoor area complete with a garden shed. The piece de resistance is the Drysdale Recreation Reserve situated at your back door. Wake every more to a chorus from the local Magpie group.
Comprising two spacious bedrooms with triple BIRs. There is a third bedroom - sitting room off the lounge area. The lounge is perfectly positioned with access to the garden area which has a northerly aspect and as the seasons change snuggle up near the cosy gas log fire.
The kitchen dining area is spacious with loads of cupboard space and dishwasher and provides access to the rear garden. A single car garage with remote and plenty of parking space. These units are in great demand in today's market so do not waste time booking your inspection

Description:
Drysdale Developers Dream!
This exclusive and limited opportunity to secure a prime land holding right in the heart of Drysdale presents an enviable opportunity to develop a potential boutique land subdivision.
-Land Holding: 13,770m2 ( 3.4 acres) approximately
-Zoning: Residential Growth Zone
Drysdale is quickly establishing itself as the 'hub' of the Bellarine and is experiencing a real estate boom. Highly regarded schooling options, well equipped medical infrasture, beautiful parklands, a developed retail hub, close proximity to award winning wineries, a vibrant restaurant and cafe scene, a short commute to Geelong CBD and easy access to a number of beautiful beaches are just a few reasons why Drysdale is a property 'hot spot'.
An unprecedented demand for land in the local property market ensures this real estate holding offers a wonderful opportunity for a savvy developer with a vision.

Description:
PERIOD CHARM , RENOVATED WITH LOVE TO DELIGHT!
"Sassafras" is one of Drysdale's earliest cottages, featuring original period charm that has been married beautifully with today's modern livability. Surrounded by an idyllic garden of fruit trees and easy care planting. Enhanced by its location, just a short stroll to the village, allowing a carefree lifestyle to enjoy cafes and the local services and only a four minute drive to the nearest beach.
With garden views from every room, light-filled "Sassafras" features open plan living, a fully renovated country kitchen, lounge and dining, all opening to the outdoor space. Two bedrooms, main with built in robes, luxuriously renovated bathroom and a large laundry. French doors lead to the freestanding undercover alfresco area. Features include ceiling rosettes, high ceilings, Baltic floors, quality fixtures & fittings , dishwasher, central heating, ceiling fans and a beautiful feature picture window. Garden shed and side access off road allows for 3 vehicles.
Live with color in your life, enjoy life on the Bellarine Peninsula.

Description:
WHEN DOWNSIZING DOESN'T FEEL LIKE DOWNSIZING!
This very spacious property is presented in as new condition and is ready to move into. Situated in a group of 8 'units' that are more like small houses. This property comes with a generously proportioned lounge room that leads through to a tiled kitchen/meals area. This area gives you access to the rear garden through double sliding doors. Internal access from the garage is a real bonus in bad weather! Both bedrooms are large and have built in robes. A central bathroom and separate toilet complete this property. Lovely fixtures and fittings throughout. Central gas heating, reverse cycle split system, gas and electric cooking, ceiling fans and much more. The gardens are neat but you could certainly add some finishing touches if you like. If you have any questions or would like to arrange an inspection call me now.

Description:
Everything At Arms Reach!...
Price Reduced.....Vendor Very Keen To Sell!!..............A truly charming weatherboard residence boasts a central location right in the heart of Drysdale. Perfectly positioned to take full advantage of all the local amenities. Drysdale Primary School is literally just across the road, the bus passes right on by your front door. Your choice of 3 leading supermarkets are just a short stroll away. These features and easy access to a comprehensive medical services hub ensures this property has and always will continue to be in high demand for the owner occupier or the savvy investor.
Upon entry you will be impressed by various original features including polished timber floor boards, commanding high ceilings with decorative cornices and generous windows that ensure an abundance of natural light. An open plan kitchen offers a user friendly and practical layout with excellent storage solutions.
All three bedrooms are genuine doubles and the main bedroom is complete with built in robes.
The property is fully fenced providing a private and secure front yard. An expansive timber decked entertaining area looks a great place for a BBQ with friends.
A long serving tenant has expressed a keen interest to stay at the property which provides an investor with a secure income stream from day 1. It's an oldie but a goodie 'location location location' and this property looks set to offer the incoming owner great capital growth prospects by virtue of its unrivalled position.

Description:
A Stonebridge Gem!
The Facts:
-A beautifully appointed 4 bedroom home boasting 3 living areas of generous proportions
-In 'as new' condition and a build of no compromise
-A lovely free flowing floor plan which creates a light and bright welcoming 'home' feel
-Set within Drysdale's tightly held Central Walk Estate and surrounded by quality built homes
-Quality fixtures and fittings throughout; a number of inclusions to be discovered upon inspection.
The Features:
Without any hesitation I can proudly say this property offers one of the most pleasant inspections in today's property market... it simply feels like 'home' from the moment you step inside. Light and bright finishes are enhanced by high ceilings and a lovely orientation to capture an abundance of natural light. An overly generous kitchen/family/meals zone takes pride of place as the 'hub' of the property; dual glass stacker sliding doors offer a seamless connection to a built in alfresco area and a generous rear yard. A beautifully appointed kitchen serves up a practical working space with excellent storage solutions; stone bench tops, stainless steel appliances and a feature tiled splashback showcase eye catching finishes. A flexible floor plan is further enhanced by 3 defined living areas to provide a range of living arrangements. All the modern comforts; ducted heating and split system cooling provide a home for all seasons. A double garage (remote controlled access) and established low maintenance gardens complete a very pretty picture. The Central Walk Estate has established itself as a premiere local real estate 'pocket'; beautiful wetlands, various walking tracks and all the conveniences of Drysdale Central all within walking distance.

Description:
Purpose built for Horse Enthusiasts
Offering the rural lifestyle 40 acres affords yet located just 5 minutes from the local beaches of Portarlington, Indented Head and St Leonards, and the heart of Drysdale shopping centre. Sundance Ranch is a purpose built horse property with particular attention given to the layout with a laneway paddock system, holding yards, wash bay,13 paddocks, electric fencing throughout, round yard, cattle yards and a 30m x 30m floodlight sand arena. The property is suitable for your enjoyment also lending itself to agistment, breeding, horse training and education. The home is set back from the road and nestled privately amongst trees and consists of 4 bedrooms, master complete with walk in robe and ensuite, open plan lounge and formal dining, gallery style kitchen with stainless steel appliances, ample storage and breakfast bar overlooking the family room that flows to the rumpus room at the rear of the home. Other features include ducted vacuum, gas heating, split system cooling and large laundry/mud room. Outside the paved patio and barbecue areas is conveniently accessed by the main living room for entertaining. For the country lifestyle so close to town this property offers it all.
Due Diligence checklist are available at www.consumer.vic.gov.au/duediligencechecklist

Description:
Boutique Build Opportunity
Build and live here at 'Central Walk' Estate, and you will be glad you did!
Waterhaven Boulevard is undoubtedly the jewel of this masterfully designed quality estate. This generous sized block sits on a subtle curve, adding further interest to the excellent aspect of this land parcel. The gentle slope from north-to-south overlooks uninterrupted views of the greenway, featuring beautiful landscaped pathways with wetlands and recreation park area.
The orientation of the build has wonderful scope for a private northern rear aspect, perfect for the main living area. The block is nestled amid an attractive streetscape, with heritage-style street lamps and well-established trees. The parcel itself is cleared and ready for excavation, and the northern and eastern boundary fencing is complete.
The location is truly superb, with only a stone's throw to the heart of charming Drysdale. The lifestyle opportunities abound here for only 20 minutes from Geelong. Ideal proximity to all the fantastic schools nearby, the beaches, the historic town of Queenscliff and the marina of Portarlington. In a highly sought after estate, chances like this will not last. Inspect today!
- Select a builder of your choice.
- Approximate land size 611m2
- Live in the heart of The Bellarine
- Locale is only 200 m from Drysdale's town centre
- Boutique development of only 200 lots (approx)
- An outstanding urban design with desirable amenities.

Description:
WHAT A POSITION , FORGET THE CAR , NOTHING TO DO.
Situated in the hub of the Drysdale village , you can walk everywhere, shops, parklands and all amenities on your doorstep. This home has the advantage of low maintenance yet providing ample living. Gracious entrance, through to large open plan area which includes dining, living and kitchen all overlooking a light filled private front courtyard. Three bedrooms , main with WIR and others with BIR's, central 2 way bathroom and powder room. A matured leafy garden with an outdoor area to relax with privacy. Features include split system , gas heater, pantry , dishwasher, quality window furnishings, outdoor shutters and loads of storage. A single garage with space for 2 more vehicles. Perfect living in this prime position.

Description:
Tuscan-inspired paradise with stunning bay views
Six acres of black cracking soil on Mt Bellarine affords incredible bay and district views and includes four acres under vine.
The gardens surrounding this Tuscan-inspired homestead are superb, exotic and verdant. The paved courtyard with pizza oven and semi commercial kitchen and garage is overseen by glorious palms and exotic trees.
Comprising five bedrooms, three living areas and study, all with beautiful aspects. A combination of architectural features such as French doors, concrete floors, timber lining and lofty ceilings promote space and light. The two bathrooms and kitchen are stylish and modern. Caesar stone tops, handmade cabinetry and quality appliances form the best of the spacious, dining/family area sandwiched between the courtyard and the vineyard. An entertainer’s delight, you will be able to serve your own shiraz, viognier, pinot gris or sauvignon blanc with grapes from your vineyard. These grapes have won gold and silver medals.
Over 70,000 litres of tank water is supplemented by town water. Near new detached double garage/shed plus garage which cleverly can be used as an alfresco area, perfect for cellar door sales and functions.
A unique slice of semi-rural living only half an hour from Geelong, you can live la dolce vita!
For further information text '221 WHITCOMBES' to 0428 444 841

Description:
BLISS ON THE BELLARINE, CUSTOM BUILT ON APP. 2 ACRES. GREAT SUB-DIVISION POTENTIAL STCA.
Situated in the middle of the Drysdale village, walking distance to town, schools and parklands, so many choices available here, develop, extended living or enjoy the parkland atmosphere. Impressive immediately with wrap around verandah and lush gardens with fruit trees and herb garden, all picture perfect. Gracious entrance and hallway, separate lounge room, second generous open plan area combining living, meals and well equipped kitchen, french doors opening to verandah with the north light a real bonus, outdoor undercover entertaining space as well. Three spacious bedrooms, master with large ensuite, BIR'S in all bedrooms, study, central bathroom, separate toilet and laundry. Features include period features, bay windows, rosettes, french doors, fretwork, cornices, polished floors, central heating, split system, pantry, dishwasher, quality fittings and so much more. Easy access with wide driveway to big garage (3ph power) plenty of room for 6 cars. Quality living in Drysdale, have a pony, gourmet vineyard, work from home on the Bellarine Peninsula.

Description:
'Camiano' Prestigious Property on 5.45 Acres
High set with exquisite views over beautiful Port Phillip Bay and the neighbouring Manzanillo Olive Grove, this well positioned property entices you beyond its lush garden frontage and contrasting contemporary exterior; sweeping you up in the romance of never wanting to leave home. Prestigious in position, individual in design, welcome to 'Camiano'.
-This stunning rural vista boasts a beautiful open plan living zone, bathed in north sun with unrivalled rural aspects
-Heightened glazing encapsulates Port Phillip Bay views, dually flooding the interior with striking botanical outlooks
-Traditional in design, the u-shaped kitchen has a 900mm gas cooktop, timber benchtops and walk in pantry
-Bespoke joinery adds an individual touch to the meals area, with french doors linking the outdoors
-A north facing pergola entangled in grapevines is the ideal setting for relaxation, overlooking the crescent shaped pool
-This enviable outdoor entertainment area is complete with pizza oven, barbeque and under mounted sink
-Offering a well structured layout with three oversized bedrooms, each featuring their own unique elements
-Luxurious in scale, the master suite boasts a walk in robe, ensuite and separate sitting area/office space
-Baltic timber floors, heightened ceilings and Cedar louvres feature throughout the well designed home
-The same extraordinary views are enjoyed in the second living area, warmed by an ambient Coonara wood fire
-Additional accommodation is provided in the self contained “Granny Flat”, with kitchenette and bathroom
-Vehicles and equipment are easily sheltered within the abundant shedding and parking space available
-4 x rainwater tanks, vegetable garden beds, secure double gated access and an alarm system are further assets
-Olive Grove plantations are productive yet low-care, gifting option as a hobby or potential business venture (STCA)
-Embrace the local culture, with award winning wineries, local produce and culinary experiences nearby
-A short distance from under-populated bay beaches and both Drysdale and Clifton Springs townships
A beautifully welcoming lifestyle property of 5.45 acres, incomparable in the current market. An inspection will impress.

Description:
Endless Opportunities
Positioned in an area steeped in history, Drysdale House dates back to 1891 and formed part of the Australian house museum. Relocated, renovated & restored, this property has been transformed to enjoy a flexible floorplan of either 4 bedrooms plus study and 4 living areas or a 6 bedroom family home, 3 bathrooms, 2 living areas, study and alfresco entertaining. Set over 2 storeys, entering the property you are taken back to the Victorian era with Baltic Pine lining, original fireplaces, formal lounge, ball and claw foot bath and high ceilings that flow through to the Master Built modern extension with open plan kitchen meals dining area, sunken rumpus room and alfresco entertaining; Upstairs comprises 2 bedrooms both with WIR, study and large central bathroom come ensuite to the master with separate W.C. Set on 710 sq meters of land, the English Cottage gardens assist in making this property a warm and inviting home ideal for the extended family, retiree or savvy business minded person looking for something with huge potential and endless opportunities.

Description:
Executive Tranquillity!
The Facts:
-A luxuriously appointed architectural design set within a beautiful tree lined cul de sac
-A contemporary open plan design delivers a wonderfully light and bright experience
-3 generous bedrooms; master complete with full ensuite and floor to ceiling mirrored walk in robes
-High raking ceilings, doubled glazed windows and top shelf finishes throughout
-Landscaped gardens provide a lovely private and tranquil setting
-A double garage (6m x 7.2m approx) with remote controlled access
-A++ central location places you walking distance to Drysdale Central and some beautiful parklands
The Features
Boasting a genuine architectural flare and set within what is recognised as one of Drysdale's exclusive pockets, this fine property sure to appeal to a buyer who has an eye for 'quality'. A beautifully appointed 'minimalist' build blends rendered brick and shadow cladding finishes to ensure it sits softly within its green leafy surrounds. Clever engineering and design provides some wonderful window features; full span floor to ceiling glass panels perfectly frame landscaped gardens, various port windows provide lovely filtered light and a spectacular glass ceiling feature in the ensuite will literally put 'stars in your eyes' as you relax in a bubble bath with a glass of your favourite wine from one of your local Bellarine Peninsula wineries. A contemporary open plan design showcases high raked ceilings, doubled glazed windows and top shelf finishes throughout to further endorse this property as one of the finest of its kind in the property market. A stunning decked alfresco offers a lovely northerly orientation and is boarded by an established hedge to provide a private setting for entertaining friends and family. An overly generous double garage (with remote controlled access) offers potentially so much more than simply accommodation for 2 cars. A second to none central location places you right in the heart of Drysdale; walking distance to all amenities and some stunning parklands. A true one of a kind in the property market and a 'must see'.
Insights: 2/10 Marsh Court, Drysdale VIC 3222 was last sold in 2019 and 22 other 3 bedroom house in Drysdale have recently been sold.

Description:
GREAT LOCATION GREAT OPPORTUNITY!!!
Situated in a quiet court in a fantastic location, this home sits on an approximately 781m2 block. It is the ideal home for those seeking the next family home or even an investment opportunity. Large grassy front yard perfect to park your caravan and boat on. An easy-living package made all the more attractive by its convenient location within walking distance to shopping precinct.

A double garage gives access to the rear yard and an undercover entertaining area with minimal maintenance required in the garden. Description:
Meticulously Maintained, Prime Location AND Views !!
Inspection of this majestic sandstone residence is a must if searching for a quality home in central Drysdale. Ernstine Way is a quiet tree-lined street within walking distance to the Drysdale shopping precinct and recreational pursuits. The property has been meticulously maintained with an eye for detail both internally and externally. Low maintenance, manicured gardens and a partially enclosed outdoor entertaining area add to the finishing touches of this lovely home.
The home oozes style from the lofty formal entrance hall to the palatial master suite and living areas. Spaciousness abounds throughout the interior of the home with the modern kitchen forming the hub of the family living space. A gas log fire is a stylish addition. The minor bedrooms at the rear are spacious and include walk-in robes and study nooks. Storage spaces are at a premium throughout. Upstairs the formal living retreat has access to views of Corio Bay from the balcony.
Features throughout include
New alarm system
SS appliances, ample bench space, vinyl wrap cabinetry, storage draws
Ducted heating & cooling
TV points to all areas including outdoor entertaining with water feature
Over height ceilings
Ensuite with twin vanity
Rear area access from the garage
A property not to be overlooked ! Inspection a must

Description:
Build your dream home close town
Wonderful opportunity to acquire an acre of land within walking distance to the centre of town. Bordered by maturing trees there is a sense of privacy.
There are establishing trees planted throughout so you don't have to wait years & a clear area to build your dream home of how many squares you like.
A two minute drive & you are at Christian College, Drysdale Primary School, in the third minute your are shopping at Coles, Aldi or Safeway.
Easy drive to Portarlington with no traffic lights to catch the Port Phillip Ferry to Melbourne Docklands.
Local restaurant wineries like Jack Rabbit, Terindah & Bellarine Estate are just minutes drive down the road.
This is an exciting opportunity to establish yourself on the Bellarine Peninsula in the central hub of Drysdale.
